<pre class="metadata">
title: Intl Sequence Units
stage: 0
contributors: Shane F Carr
</pre>

<emu-clause id="ecma402-locales-currencies-tz">
  <h1>Identification of Locales, Currencies, Time Zones, Measurement Units, Numbering Systems, Collations, and Calendars</h1>

  <emu-clause id="sec-measurement-unit-identifiers">
    <h1>Measurement Unit Identifiers</h1>

    <p>This specification identifies measurement units using a <dfn variants="core unit identifiers,core unit ID,core unit IDs">core unit identifier</dfn> (or equivalently <em>core unit ID</em>) as defined by <a href="https://unicode.org/reports/tr35/tr35-general.html#Unit_Identifiers">Unicode Technical Standard #35 Part 2 General, Section 6.2 Unit Identifiers</a>. Their canonical form is a string containing only Unicode Basic Latin lowercase letters (U+0061 LATIN SMALL LETTER A through U+007A LATIN SMALL LETTER Z) with zero or more medial hyphens (U+002D HYPHEN-MINUS).</p>

    <p>
      Only a limited set of core unit identifiers are sanctioned.
      Attempting to use an unsanctioned core unit identifier results in a *RangeError*.
    </p>

    <emu-clause id="sec-iswellformedunitidentifier" type="abstract operation">
      <h1>
        IsWellFormedUnitIdentifier (
          _unitIdentifier_: a String,
        ): a Boolean
      </h1>
      <dl class="header">
        <dt>description</dt>
        <dd>It verifies that the _unitIdentifier_ argument represents a well-formed core unit identifier that is either a sanctioned single unit or a complex unit formed by division of two sanctioned single units.</dd>
      </dl>
      <emu-alg>
        1. If IsSanctionedSingleUnitIdentifier(_unitIdentifier_) is *true*, then
          1. Return *true*.
        1. <ins>Let _sequence_ be StringSplitToList(_unitIdentifier_, *"-and-"*).</ins>
        1. <ins>If the length of _sequence_ &gt; 1, then</ins>
          1. <ins>For each row _row_ of <emu-xref href="#table-sanctioned-sequence-unit-groups"></emu-xref>, do</ins>
            1. <ins>Let _group_ be the list of simple unit identifiers listed in the Sequence column of _row_.</ins>
            1. <ins>If _group_ contains _sequence_[0], then</ins>
              1. <ins>If any of the elements of _sequence_ are not in _group_, return *false*.</ins>
              1. <ins>If the elements of _sequence_ are not in the same order as they are in _group_, return *false*.</ins>
              1. <ins>Return *true*.</ins>
          1. <ins>Return *false*.</ins>
        1. <del>Let _i_ be StringIndexOf(_unitIdentifier_, *"-per-"*, 0).</del>
        1. <del>If _i_ is ~not-found~ or StringIndexOf(_unitIdentifier_, *"-per-"*, _i_ + 1) is not ~not-found~, then</del>
          1. <del>Return *false*.</del>
        1. <del>Assert: The five-character substring *"-per-"* occurs exactly once in _unitIdentifier_, at index _i_.</del>
        1. <ins>Let _per_ be StringSplitToList(_unitIdentifier_, *"-per-"*).</ins>
        1. <ins>If the length of _per_ is not 2, return *false*.</ins>
        1. Let _numerator_ be <del>the substring of _unitIdentifier_ from 0 to _i_</del> <ins>_per_[0]</ins>.
        1. Let _denominator_ be <del>the substring of _unitIdentifier_ from _i_ + 5</del> <ins>_per_[1]</ins>.
        1. If IsSanctionedSingleUnitIdentifier(_numerator_) and IsSanctionedSingleUnitIdentifier(_denominator_) are both *true*, then
          1. Return *true*.
        1. Return *false*.
      </emu-alg>

      <ins class="block">
      <emu-table id="table-sanctioned-sequence-unit-groups">
        <emu-caption>Sanctioned Sequence Unit Groups</emu-caption>
        <table class="real-table">
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th>Sequence</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr><td>« *"mile"*, *"yard"*, *"foot"*, *"inch"* »</td></tr>
            <tr><td>« *"kilometer"*, *"meter"*, *"centimeter"*, *"millimeter"* »</td></tr>
            <tr><td>« *"stone"*, *"pound"*, *"ounce"* »</td></tr>
            <tr><td>« *"kilogram"*, *"gram"* »</td></tr>
            <tr><td>« *"gallon"*, *"fluid-ounce"* »</td></tr>
            <tr><td>« *"liter"*, *"milliliter"* »</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </emu-table>
      </ins>
    </emu-clause>
  </emu-clause>
</emu-clause>

<emu-clause id="numberformat-objects">
  <h1>NumberFormat Objects</h1>

  <emu-clause id="sec-properties-of-intl-numberformat-prototype-object">
    <h1>Properties of the Intl.NumberFormat Prototype Object</h1>

    <p>The <dfn>Intl.NumberFormat prototype object</dfn>:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>is <dfn>%Intl.NumberFormat.prototype%</dfn>.</li>
      <li>is an ordinary object.</li>
      <li>is not an Intl.NumberFormat instance and does not have an [[InitializedNumberFormat]] internal slot or any of the other internal slots of Intl.NumberFormat instance objects.</li>
      <li>has a [[Prototype]] internal slot whose value is %Object.prototype%.</li>
    </ul>

    <emu-clause id="sec-number-format-functions">
      <h1>Number Format Functions</h1>

      <p>A Number format function is an anonymous built-in function that has a [[NumberFormat]] internal slot.</p>
      <p>When a Number format function _F_ is called with optional argument _value_, the following steps are taken:</p>

      <emu-alg>
        1. Let _nf_ be _F_.[[NumberFormat]].
        1. Assert: _nf_ is an Object and _nf_ has an [[InitializedNumberFormat]] internal slot.
        1. If _value_ is not provided, let _value_ be *undefined*.
        1. <ins>If _nf_.[[Style]] is *"unit"* and StringIndexOf(_nf_.[[Unit]], *"-and-"*, 0) is not ~not-found~, then</ins>
          1. <ins>Let _values_ be ? ToSequenceUnitList(_nf_.[[Unit]], _value_).</ins>
          1. <ins>Return FormatNumericSequence(_nf_, _values_).</ins>
        1. Let _x_ be ? ToIntlMathematicalValue(_value_).
        1. Return FormatNumeric(_nf_, _x_).
      </emu-alg>

      <p>The *"length"* property of a Number format function is *1*<sub>𝔽</sub>.</p>
    </emu-clause>

    <emu-clause id="sec-intl.numberformat.prototype.formattoparts">
      <h1>Intl.NumberFormat.prototype.formatToParts ( _value_ )</h1>

      <p>When the `formatToParts` method is called with an optional argument _value_, the following steps are taken:</p>

      <emu-alg>
        1. Let _nf_ be the *this* value.
        1. Perform ? RequireInternalSlot(_nf_, [[InitializedNumberFormat]]).
        1. <ins>If _nf_.[[Style]] is *"unit"* and StringIndexOf(_nf_.[[Unit]], *"-and-"*, 0) is not ~not-found~, then</ins>
          1. <ins>Let _values_ be ? ToSequenceUnitList(_nf_.[[Unit]], _value_).</ins>
          1. <ins>Return FormatNumericSequenceToParts(_nf_, _values_).</ins>
        1. Let _x_ be ? ToIntlMathematicalValue(_value_).
        1. Return FormatNumericToParts(_nf_, _x_).
      </emu-alg>
    </emu-clause>
  </emu-clause>

  <emu-clause id="sec-numberformat-abstracts">
    <h1>Abstract Operations for NumberFormat Objects</h1>

    <ins class="block">
    <emu-clause id="sec-tosequenceunitlist" type="abstract operation">
      <h1>
        ToSequenceUnitList (
          _unit_: a String,
          _value_: an ECMAScript language value,
        ): either a normal completion containing a List of Intl mathematical values, or a throw completion
      </h1>
      <dl class="header">
      </dl>
      <emu-alg>
        1. If _value_ is not an Object, throw a *TypeError* exception.
        1. Let _sequence_ be StringSplitToList(_unit_, *"-and-"*).
        1. Let _values_ be a new empty List.
        1. Let _hasNegative_ be *false*.
        1. Let _hasPositive_ be *false*.
        1. Let _hasNonInteger_ be *false*.
        1. Let _i_ be 0.
        1. For each String _subUnit_ of _sequence_, do
          1. If _i_ is the length of _sequence_ - 1, let _isLast_ be *true*; else let _isLast_ be *false*.
          1. Let _subValue_ be ? Get(_value_, _subUnit_).
          1. If _subValue_ is *undefined*, throw a *TypeError* exception.
          1. Let _x_ be ? ToIntlMathematicalValue(_subValue_).
          1. If _isLast_ is *false* and _x_ is not an integer, set _hasNonInteger_ to *true*.
          1. If _x_ &lt; 0, set _hasNegative_ to *true*.
          1. If _x_ &gt; 0, set _hasPositive_ to *true*.
          1. Append _x_ to _values_.
          1. Set _i_ to _i_ + 1.
        1. If _hasNegative_ is *true* and _hasPositive_ is *true*, throw a *RangeError* exception.
        1. If _hasNonInteger_ is *true*, throw a *RangeError* exception.
        1. Return _values_.
      </emu-alg>
    </emu-clause>
    </ins>

    <ins class="block">
    <emu-clause id="sec-formatnumericsequence" type="abstract operation">
      <h1>
        FormatNumericSequence (
          _numberFormat_: an Intl.NumberFormat,
          _values_: a List of Intl mathematical values,
        ): a String
      </h1>
      <dl class="header">
      </dl>
      <emu-alg>
        1. Let _parts_ be PartitionSequenceUnitPattern(_numberFormat_, _values_).
        1. Let _result_ be the empty String.
        1. For each Record { [[Type]], [[Value]] } _part_ of _parts_, do
          1. Set _result_ to the string-concatenation of _result_ and _part_.[[Value]].
        1. Return _result_.
      </emu-alg>
    </emu-clause>
    </ins>

    <ins class="block">
    <emu-clause id="sec-formatnumericsequencetoparts" type="abstract operation">
      <h1>
        FormatNumericSequenceToParts (
          _numberFormat_: an Intl.NumberFormat,
          _values_: a List of Intl mathematical values,
        ): an Array
      </h1>
      <dl class="header">
      </dl>
      <emu-alg>
        1. Let _parts_ be PartitionSequenceUnitPattern(_numberFormat_, _values_).
        1. Let _result_ be ! ArrayCreate(0).
        1. Let _n_ be 0.
        1. For each Record { [[Type]], [[Value]] } _part_ of _parts_, do
          1. Let _O_ be OrdinaryObjectCreate(%Object.prototype%).
          1. Perform ! CreateDataPropertyOrThrow(_O_, *"type"*, _part_.[[Type]]).
          1. Perform ! CreateDataPropertyOrThrow(_O_, *"value"*, _part_.[[Value]]).
          1. Perform ! CreateDataPropertyOrThrow(_result_, ! ToString(𝔽(_n_)), _O_).
          1. Increment _n_ by 1.
        1. Return _result_.
      </emu-alg>
    </emu-clause>
    </ins>

    <ins class="block">
    <emu-clause id="sec-partitionsequenceunitpattern" type="abstract operation">
      <h1>
        PartitionSequenceUnitPattern (
          _numberFormat_: an Intl.NumberFormat,
          _values_: a List of Intl mathematical values,
        ): a List of Records with fields [[Type]] (a String) and [[Value]] (a String)
      </h1>
      <dl class="header">
      </dl>
      <emu-alg>
        1. Assert: _numberFormat_.[[Style]] is *"unit"* and StringIndexOf(_numberFormat_.[[Unit]], *"-and-"*, 0) is not ~not-found~.
        1. Let _sequence_ be StringSplitToList(_numberFormat_.[[Unit]], *"-and-"*).
        1. Let _partitionedPartsList_ be a new empty List.
        1. Let _lfOpts_ be OrdinaryObjectCreate(*null*).
        1. Perform ! CreateDataPropertyOrThrow(_lfOpts_, *"type"*, *"unit"*).
        1. Perform ! CreateDataPropertyOrThrow(_lfOpts_, *"style"*, _numberFormat_.[[UnitDisplay]]).
        1. Let _lf_ be ! Construct(%Intl.ListFormat%, « _numberFormat_.[[Locale]], _lfOpts_ »).
        1. Let _strings_ be a new empty List.
        1. Let _originalUnit_ be _numberFormat_.[[Unit]].
        1. Let _originalRoundingType_ be _numberFormat_.[[RoundingType]].
        1. Let _originalMinFD_ be _numberFormat_.[[MinimumFractionDigits]].
        1. Let _originalMaxFD_ be _numberFormat_.[[MaximumFractionDigits]].
        1. Let _originalMinSD_ be _numberFormat_.[[MinimumSignificantDigits]].
        1. Let _originalMaxSD_ be _numberFormat_.[[MaximumSignificantDigits]].
        1. Let _i_ be 0.
        1. For each Intl mathematical value _x_ of _values_, do
          1. If _i_ is 0, let _isFirst_ be *true*; else let _isFirst_ be *false*.
          1. If _i_ is the length of _sequence_ - 1, let _isLast_ be *true*; else let _isLast_ be *false*.
          1. If _isFirst_ is *false*, then
            1. If _x_ &lt; 0, set _x_ to -_x_.
            1. If _x_ is negative-zero, set _x_ to 0.
          1. Let _subUnit_ be _sequence_[_i_].
          1. Set _numberFormat_.[[Unit]] to _subUnit_.
          1. If _isLast_ is *false*, then
            1. Set _numberFormat_.[[RoundingType]] to ~fraction-digits~.
            1. Set _numberFormat_.[[MinimumFractionDigits]] to 0.
            1. Set _numberFormat_.[[MaximumFractionDigits]] to 3.
          1. Else,
            1. Set _numberFormat_.[[RoundingType]] to _originalRoundingType_.
            1. Set _numberFormat_.[[MinimumFractionDigits]] to _originalMinFD_.
            1. Set _numberFormat_.[[MaximumFractionDigits]] to _originalMaxFD_.
            1. Set _numberFormat_.[[MinimumSignificantDigits]] to _originalMinSD_.
            1. Set _numberFormat_.[[MaximumSignificantDigits]] to _originalMaxSD_.
          1. Let _parts_ be PartitionNumberPattern(_numberFormat_, _x_).
          1. Append _parts_ to _partitionedPartsList_.
          1. Let _string_ be the empty String.
          1. For each Record { [[Type]], [[Value]] } _part_ in _parts_, do
            1. Set _string_ to the string-concatenation of _string_ and _part_.[[Value]].
          1. Append _string_ to _strings_.
          1. Set _i_ to _i_ + 1.
        1. Set _numberFormat_.[[Unit]] to _originalUnit_.
        1. Let _formattedPartsList_ be CreatePartsFromList(_lf_, _strings_).
        1. Let _flattenedPartsList_ be a new empty List.
        1. Let _partitionedPartsIndex_ be 0.
        1. NOTE: The following loop substitutes the formatted elements returned by CreatePartsFromList with the detailed parts saved in _partitionedPartsList_.
        1. For each Record { [[Type]], [[Value]] } _listPart_ in _formattedPartsList_, do
          1. If _listPart_.[[Type]] is *"element"*, then
            1. Let _parts_ be _partitionedPartsList_[_partitionedPartsIndex_].
            1. Append the elements of _parts_ to _flattenedPartsList_.
            1. Set _partitionedPartsIndex_ to _partitionedPartsIndex_ + 1.
          1. Else,
            1. Assert: _listPart_.[[Type]] is *"literal"*.
            1. Append _listPart_ to _flattenedPartsList_.
        1. Return _flattenedPartsList_.
      </emu-alg>
    </emu-clause>
    </ins>
  </emu-clause>
</emu-clause>
